This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human action recognition in 3D skeleton sequences. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques such as LSTM networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

As the paper deals with video data, it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, as the paper proposes a new class of LSTM network, it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
